  "description": "Minor arcana interpretations combine suit themes with rank themes.\n¶Suit themes Wands: drive, growth, creative force. Cups: emotion, relationships, receptivity. Swords: thought, conflict, clarity. Pentacles: material life, craft, stability. ¶Rank themes Ace: beginnings, seed. Two: balance, choice. Three: expansion, collaboration. Four: stability, rest. Five: tension, challenge. Six: adjustment, movement. Seven: strategy, assessment. Eight: momentum, focus. Nine: fruition, endurance. Ten: completion, burden. Page: learning, curiosity. Knight: action, pursuit. Queen: mastery, nurture. King: leadership, command. ¶Wands Ace of Wands: beginnings of drive and creativity. Two of Wands: choosing a direction for growth. Three of Wands: expansion through collaboration. Four of Wands: stable momentum and celebration. Five of Wands: tension in creative forces. Six of Wands: recognition and forward movement. Seven of Wands: defensive strategy and assessment. Eight of Wands: rapid motion and focus. Nine of Wands: endurance under pressure. Ten of Wands: completion with heavy burden. Page of Wands: learning a new spark. Knight of Wands: acting on creative pursuit. Queen of Wands: nurtured confidence and mastery. King of Wands: leading with vision and drive. ¶Cups Ace of Cups: beginnings of emotion and connection. Two of Cups: balance and mutual exchange. Three of Cups: shared joy and collaboration. Four of Cups: stability, rest, or disengagement. Five of Cups: emotional tension and loss. Six of Cups: movement through memory and care. Seven of Cups: assessment of emotional options. Eight of Cups: focused departure or pursuit. Nine of Cups: fruition and emotional endurance. Ten of Cups: completion of relational harmony. Page of Cups: learning emotional expression. Knight of Cups: acting on feeling or invitation. Queen of Cups: nurtured empathy and depth. King of Cups: leadership through steady feeling. ¶Swords Ace of Swords: beginnings of clarity and resolve. Two of Swords: balance or stalemate in thought. Three of Swords: expansion into conflict or pain. Four of Swords: stable rest and recovery. Five of Swords: tension through conflict. Six of Swords: movement toward calmer clarity. Seven of Swords: strategy and careful assessment. Eight of Swords: focused pressure or restriction. Nine of Swords: endurance through worry. Ten of Swords: completion through rupture. Page of Swords: learning critical thinking. Knight of Swords: acting with sharp pursuit. Queen of Swords: mastery of clarity and honesty. King of Swords: leadership through reason. ¶Pentacles Ace of Pentacles: beginnings in material life. Two of Pentacles: balancing resources. Three of Pentacles: collaborative craft and growth. Four of Pentacles: stability and holding. Five of Pentacles: material tension or scarcity. Six of Pentacles: adjustment through exchange. Seven of Pentacles: assessment of growth. Eight of Pentacles: focused practice and work. Nine of Pentacles: fruition and independence. Ten of Pentacles: completion and legacy. Page of Pentacles: learning practical skills. Knight of Pentacles: steady pursuit and effort. Queen of Pentacles: nurtured stability and care. King of Pentacles: leadership through material command. ",
